snippet: The government received the go-ahead on Wednesday to remove tents that Palestinian activists had pitched on a patch of West Bank land marked for Jewish settlements.
abstract: Israel's Supreme Court gives government go-ahead to remove tents that Palestinian activists had pitched on patch of West Bank land marked for Jewish settlements.
lead_paragraph: The government received the go-ahead on Wednesday to remove tents that Palestinian activists had pitched on a patch of West Bank land marked for Jewish settlements.

headline.main: Israeli Court Allows Removal of Tents in ‘E1’ Area
